Text: CLINTON: No.
Speech: No.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: There are many people who believe that the only way we can get this country turned around is to tax the middle class more and punish them more, but the truth is that middle-class Americans are basically the only group of Americans who've been taxed more in the 1980s and during the last 12 years, even though their incomes have gone down.
Speech: There are many people who believe that the only way we can get this country turned around is to tax the middle class more and punish them more, but the truth is that middle-class Americans are basically the only group of Americans who've been taxed more in the 1980s and during the last 12 years, even though their incomes have gone down.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: The wealthiest Americans have been taxed much less, even though their incomes have gone up.
Speech: The wealthiest Americans have been taxed much less, even though their incomes have gone up.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Middle-class people will have their fair share of changing to do, and many challenges to face, including the challenge of becoming constantly re-educated.
Speech: Middle-class people will have their fair share of changing to do, and many challenges to face, including the challenge of becoming constantly re-educated.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: But my plan is a departure from trickle-down economics, just cutting taxes on the wealthiest Americans and getting out of the way.
Speech: But my plan is a departure from trickle-down economics, just cutting taxes on the wealthiest Americans and getting out of the way.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: It's also a departure from tax-and- spend economics, because you can't tax and divide an economy that isn't growing.
Speech: It's also a departure from tax-and- spend economics, because you can't tax and divide an economy that isn't growing.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I propose an American version of what works in other countries -- I think we can do it better: invest and grow.
Speech: I propose an American version of what works in other countries -- I think we can do it better: invest and grow.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I believe we can increase investment and reduce the deficit at the same time, if we not only ask the wealthiest Americans and foreign corporations to pay their share; we also provide over $100 billion in tax relief, in terms of incentives for new plants, new small businesses, new technologies, new housing, and for middle class families; and we have $140 billion of spending cuts.
Speech: I believe we can increase investment and reduce the deficit at the same time, if we not only ask the wealthiest Americans and foreign corporations to pay their share; we also provide over $100 billion in tax relief, in terms of incentives for new plants, new small businesses, new technologies, new housing, and for middle class families; and we have $140 billion of spending cuts.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Invest and grow.
Speech: Invest and grow.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Raise some more money, spend the money on tax incentives to have growth in the private sector, take the money from the defense cuts and reinvest it in new transportation and communications and environmental clean-up systems.
Speech: Raise some more money, spend the money on tax incentives to have growth in the private sector, take the money from the defense cuts and reinvest it in new transportation and communications and environmental clean-up systems.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: This will work.
Speech: This will work.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: On this, as on so many other issues, I have a fundamental difference from the present administration.
Speech: On this, as on so many other issues, I have a fundamental difference from the present administration.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I don't believe trickle down economics will work.
Speech: I don't believe trickle down economics will work.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Unemployment is up.
Speech: Unemployment is up.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Most people are working harder for less money than they were making 10 years ago.
Speech: Most people are working harder for less money than they were making 10 years ago.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I think we can do better if we have the courage to change.
Speech: I think we can do better if we have the courage to change.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: BUSH: Do I have 1 minute?
Speech: Do I have 1 minute?
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: Just the ground rules here.
Speech: Just the ground rules here.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: BUSH: Well, he doesn't like trickle down government but I think he's talking about the Reagan-Bush years where we created 15 million jobs.
Speech: Well, he doesn't like trickle down government but I think he's talking about the Reagan-Bush years where we created 15 million jobs.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: The rich are paying a bigger percent of the total tax burden.
Speech: The rich are paying a bigger percent of the total tax burden.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: And what I don't like is trickle down government.
Speech: And what I don't like is trickle down government.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: And therein, I think Governor Clinton keeps talking about trickle down, trickle down, and he's still talking about spending more and taxing more.
Speech: And therein, I think Governor Clinton keeps talking about trickle down, trickle down, and he's still talking about spending more and taxing more.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: Government -- he says invest government, grow government.
Speech: Government -- he says invest government, grow government.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: Government doesn't create jobs.

Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: If they do, they're make-work jobs.
Speech: If they do, they're make-work jobs.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: It's the private sector that creates jobs.
Speech: It's the private sector that creates jobs.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: And yes, we've got too many taxes on the American people and we're spending too much.
Speech: And yes, we've got too many taxes on the American people and we're spending too much.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: And that's why I want to get the deficit down by controlling the growth of mandatory spending.
Speech: And that's why I want to get the deficit down by controlling the growth of mandatory spending.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: It won't be painless.
Speech: It won't be painless.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: I think Mr. Perot put his finger on something there.
Speech: I think Mr. Perot put his finger on something there.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: It won't be painless but we've got to get the job done.
Speech: It won't be painless but we've got to get the job done.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: But not by raising taxes.
Speech: But not by raising taxes.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: Mr. and Mrs. America, when you hear him say we're going to tax only the rich, watch your wallet because his figures don't add up and he's going to sock it right to the middle class taxpayer and lower, if he's going to pay for all the spending programs he proposes.
Speech: Mr. and Mrs. America, when you hear him say we're going to tax only the rich, watch your wallet because his figures don't add up and he's going to sock it right to the middle class taxpayer and lower, if he's going to pay for all the spending programs he proposes.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: So we have a big difference on this trickle down theory.
Speech: So we have a big difference on this trickle down theory.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: I do not want any more trickle down government.
Speech: I do not want any more trickle down government.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: It's gotten too big.
Speech: It's gotten too big.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: I want to do something about that.
Speech: I want to do something about that.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: PEROT: The basic problem with it, it doesn't balance the budget.
Speech: The basic problem with it, it doesn't balance the budget.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: If you forecast it out, we still have a significant deficit under each of their plans, as I understand them.
Speech: If you forecast it out, we still have a significant deficit under each of their plans, as I understand them.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: Our challenge is to stop the financial bleeding.
Speech: Our challenge is to stop the financial bleeding.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: If you take a patient into the hospital that's bleeding arterially, step one is to stop the bleeding.
Speech: If you take a patient into the hospital that's bleeding arterially, step one is to stop the bleeding.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: And we are bleeding arterially.
Speech: And we are bleeding arterially.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: There's only one way out of this, and that is to stop the deterioration of our job base, to have a growing, expanding job base, to give us the tax base -- see, balancing the budget is not nearly as difficult as paying off the $4 trillion debt and leaving our children the American dream intact.
Speech: There's only one way out of this, and that is to stop the deterioration of our job base, to have a growing, expanding job base, to give us the tax base -- see, balancing the budget is not nearly as difficult as paying off the $4 trillion debt and leaving our children the American dream intact.

Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: We have spent their money.
Speech: We have spent their money.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: We've got to pay it back.
Speech: We've got to pay it back.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: This is going to take fair, shared sacrifice.
Speech: This is going to take fair, shared sacrifice.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: My plan balances the budget within 6 years.
Speech: My plan balances the budget within 6 years.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: We didn't do it faster than that because we didn't want to disrupt the economy.
Speech: We didn't do it faster than that because we didn't want to disrupt the economy.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: We gave it off to a slow start and a fast finish to give the economy time to recover.
Speech: We gave it off to a slow start and a fast finish to give the economy time to recover.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: But we faced it and we did it, and we believe it's fair, shared sacrifice.
Speech: But we faced it and we did it, and we believe it's fair, shared sacrifice.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: The one thing I have done is lay it squarely on the table in front of the American people.
Speech: The one thing I have done is lay it squarely on the table in front of the American people.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: You've had a number of occasions to see in detail what the plan is, and at least you'll understand it.
Speech: You've had a number of occasions to see in detail what the plan is, and at least you'll understand it.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: I think that's fundamental in our country, that you know what you're getting into.
Speech: I think that's fundamental in our country, that you know what you're getting into.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: CLINTON: I disagree with both of them.
Speech: I disagree with both of them.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: For one thing, let me just follow up here.
Speech: For one thing, let me just follow up here.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I disagree with Mr. Perot that the answer is to raise -- put a 50-cent gas tax on the middle class and raise more taxes on the middle class and the working poor than on the wealthy.
Speech: I disagree with Mr. Perot that the answer is to raise -- put a 50-cent gas tax on the middle class and raise more taxes on the middle class and the working poor than on the wealthy.

Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: His own analysis says that unemployment will be slightly higher in 1995 under his plan than it is today.
Speech: His own analysis says that unemployment will be slightly higher in 1995 under his plan than it is today.

Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: And as far as what Mr. Bush says, he is the person who raised taxes on the middle class after saying he wouldn't.
Speech: And as far as what Mr. Bush says, he is the person who raised taxes on the middle class after saying he wouldn't.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: And just this year, Mr. Bush vetoed a tax increase on the wealthy that gave middle class tax relief.
Speech: And just this year, Mr. Bush vetoed a tax increase on the wealthy that gave middle class tax relief.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: He vetoed middle class tax relief this year.
Speech: He vetoed middle class tax relief this year.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: And furthermore, under this administration, spending has increased more than it has in the last 20 years and he asked Congress to spend more money than it actually spent.
Speech: And furthermore, under this administration, spending has increased more than it has in the last 20 years and he asked Congress to spend more money than it actually spent.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Now, it's hard to out-spend Congress but he tried to for the last 3 years.
Speech: Now, it's hard to out-spend Congress but he tried to for the last 3 years.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: So my view is the middle class is the -- they've been suffering, Jim.
Speech: So my view is the middle class is the -- they've been suffering, Jim.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Now, should people pay more for Medicare if they can?
Speech: Now, should people pay more for Medicare if they can?
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Yes.
Speech: Yes.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Should they pay more for Social Security if they get more out of it than they paid in, they're upper income people?
Speech: Should they pay more for Social Security if they get more out of it than they paid in, they're upper income people?
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Yes.
Speech: Yes.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: But look what's happened to the middle class.
Speech: But look what's happened to the middle class.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Middle class Americans are working harder for less money than they were making ten years ago and they're paying higher taxes.
Speech: Middle class Americans are working harder for less money than they were making ten years ago and they're paying higher taxes.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: The tax burden on them has not gone down.
Speech: The tax burden on them has not gone down.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: It has gone up.
Speech: It has gone up.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I don't think the answer is to slow the economy down more, drive unemployment up more and undermine the health of the private sector.
Speech: I don't think the answer is to slow the economy down more, drive unemployment up more and undermine the health of the private sector.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: The answer is to invest and grow this economy.
Speech: The answer is to invest and grow this economy.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: That's what works in other countries and that's what'll work here.
Speech: That's what works in other countries and that's what'll work here.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: BUSH: I think everybody's paying too much taxes.
Speech: I think everybody's paying too much taxes.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: He refers to one tax increase.
Speech: He refers to one tax increase.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: Let me remind you it was a Democratic tax increase, and I didn't want to do it and I went along with it.
Speech: Let me remind you it was a Democratic tax increase, and I didn't want to do it and I went along with it.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: And I said I make a mistake.
Speech: And I said I make a mistake.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: If I make a mistake, I admit it.
Speech: If I make a mistake, I admit it.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: That's quite different than some.
Speech: That's quite different than some.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: But I think that's the American way.
Speech: But I think that's the American way.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: I think everyone's paying too much, but I think this idea that you can go out and -- then he hits me for vetoing a tax bill.
Speech: I think everyone's paying too much, but I think this idea that you can go out and -- then he hits me for vetoing a tax bill.
Speaker: BUSH

Text: Yes, I did.
Speech: Yes, I did.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: And the American taxpayer ought to be glad they have a president to stand up to a spending Congress.
Speech: And the American taxpayer ought to be glad they have a president to stand up to a spending Congress.

Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: We remember what it was like when we had a spending president and a spending Congress, and interest rates -- who remembers that?

Speaker: BUSH

Text: They were at 21.5% under Jimmy Carter, and inflation was 15.
Speech: They were at 21.5% under Jimmy Carter, and inflation was 15.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: We don't want to go back to that.
Speech: We don't want to go back to that.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: And so yes, everybody's taxed too much and I want to get the taxes down, but not by signing a tax bill that's gonna raise taxes on people.
Speech: And so yes, everybody's taxed too much and I want to get the taxes down, but not by signing a tax bill that's gonna raise taxes on people.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: BUSH: Well, the record in Arkansas.
Speech: Well, the record in Arkansas.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: I mean, look at it, and that's what we're asking America to have?
Speech: I mean, look at it, and that's what we're asking America to have?
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: Now look, he says Arkansas's a poor state.
Speech: Now look, he says Arkansas's a poor state.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: They are.
Speech: They are.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Speech: But in almost every category they're lagging.

Name: George H. W. Bush

Speech: On pay for teachers, on all these categories, Arkansas is right near the very bottom.

Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: And I'm going to do that.
Speech: And I'm going to do that.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Name: George H. W. Bush

Speech: So we've got to do that.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Speech: I gotta get it in perspective.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: What's his mistake?
Speech: What's his mistake?
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Speech: Admit it, that Arkansas is doing very, very badly against any standard -- environment, support for police officers, whatever it is.

Speech: Mr. Bush's Bureau of Labor Statistics says that Arkansas ranks first in the country in the growth of new jobs this year, first.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: BUSH: This year.
Speech: This year.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Speech: 4th in manufacturing jobs, 4th in the reduction of poverty, 4th in income increase.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Speech: Over the last 10 years we've created manufacturing jobs much more rapidly than the national average.

Text: Over the last 5 years our income has grown more rapidly than the national average.

Speech: I wish America had that kind of record and I think most people looking at us tonight would like it if we had more jobs and a lower spending burden on the government.

Text: PEROT: I grew up 5 blocks from Arkansas.
Speech: I grew up 5 blocks from Arkansas.

Name: Henry Ross Perot

Name: Henry Ross Perot

Speech: It has a population less than Chicago or Los Angeles, about the size of Dallas and Forth Worth combined.

Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: CLINTON: Mr. Perot, with all respect, I think it is highly relevant, and I think that a 4-billion dollar budget of state and federal funds is not all that small, and I think the fact that I took a state that was one of the poorest states in the country and had been for 153 years and tried my best to modernize its economy and to make the kind of changes that have generated support from people like the presidents of Apple Computer and Hewlett-Packard and some of the biggest companies in this country, 24 retired generals and admirals and hundreds of business executives, are highly relevant.

Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: CLINTON: And the people who have jobs -- (APPLAUSE)  The people who have jobs and educations and opportunities that didn't have them 10 years ago don't think it's irrelevant at all; they think it's highly relevant and they wish the rest of the country had them.
Speech: And the people who have jobs -- (APPLAUSE)  The people who have jobs and educations and opportunities that didn't have them 10 years ago don't think it's irrelevant at all; they think it's highly relevant and they wish the rest of the country had them.

Text: I think it's important to elect a president who is committed to getting this economy going again, and who realizes we have to abandon trickle-down economics and put the American people first again, and who will send programs to the Congress in the first hundred days to deal with the critical issues that America is crying out for leadership on -- jobs, incomes, the health care crisis, the need to control the economy.
Speech: I think it's important to elect a president who is committed to getting this economy going again, and who realizes we have to abandon trickle-down economics and put the American people first again, and who will send programs to the Congress in the first hundred days to deal with the critical issues that America is crying out for leadership on -- jobs, incomes, the health care crisis, the need to control the economy.

Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: That's just what the president did when he vetoed the Family Leave Act.
Speech: That's just what the president did when he vetoed the Family Leave Act.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I think what he should have done is gone before the American people on the front end and said listen, I made a commitment and it was wrong.
Speech: I think what he should have done is gone before the American people on the front end and said listen, I made a commitment and it was wrong.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I made a mistake because I couldn't have foreseen these circumstances and this is the best deal we can work out at the time.
Speech: I made a mistake because I couldn't have foreseen these circumstances and this is the best deal we can work out at the time.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: He said it was in the public interest at the time and most everybody who was involved in it, I guess, thought it was.
Speech: He said it was in the public interest at the time and most everybody who was involved in it, I guess, thought it was.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: The real mistake was the "read my lips" promise in the first place.
Speech: The real mistake was the "read my lips" promise in the first place.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: You just can't promise something like that just to get elected if you know there's a good chance that circumstances may overtake you.
Speech: You just can't promise something like that just to get elected if you know there's a good chance that circumstances may overtake you.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: PEROT: You're talking about 2 different subjects.
Speech: You're talking about 2 different subjects.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: In order to lead, you first have to use the White House as a bully pulpit and lead; then you have to develop consensus or you can't get anything done, and that's where we are now.
Speech: In order to lead, you first have to use the White House as a bully pulpit and lead; then you have to develop consensus or you can't get anything done, and that's where we are now.

Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: We can't get anything done.
Speech: We can't get anything done.

Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: How do you get anything done when you've got all of these political action committees, all of these thousands of registered lobbyists -- 40,000 registered lobbyists, 23,000 special interest groups -- and the list goes on and on and on.
Speech: How do you get anything done when you've got all of these political action committees, all of these thousands of registered lobbyists -- 40,000 registered lobbyists, 23,000 special interest groups -- and the list goes on and on and on.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: And the average citizen out here is just working hard every day.
Speech: And the average citizen out here is just working hard every day.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: You've got to go to the people.
Speech: You've got to go to the people.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: I just love the fact that everybody, particularly in the media, goes bonkers over the town hall.
Speech: I just love the fact that everybody, particularly in the media, goes bonkers over the town hall.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: I guess it's because you will lose your right to tell them what to think.
Speech: I guess it's because you will lose your right to tell them what to think.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: The point is, they'll get to decide what to think.
Speech: The point is, they'll get to decide what to think.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: (Laughter and applause)  I love the fact that people will listen to a guy with a bad accent and a poor presentation manner talking about flip charts for 30 minutes, because they want the details.
Speech: (Laughter and applause)  I love the fact that people will listen to a guy with a bad accent and a poor presentation manner talking about flip charts for 30 minutes, because they want the details.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: See, all the folks up there at the top said the attention span of the American people is no more than 5 minutes, they won't watch it.
Speech: See, all the folks up there at the top said the attention span of the American people is no more than 5 minutes, they won't watch it.

Name: Henry Ross Perot

Speech: They're thirsty for it.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: You want to have a new program in this country.
Speech: You want to have a new program in this country.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: If you get grassroots America excited about it, and if they tap Congress on the shoulder and say do it, Charlie, it'll happen.
Speech: If you get grassroots America excited about it, and if they tap Congress on the shoulder and say do it, Charlie, it'll happen.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: And that's a whole lot different from these fellows running up and down the halls whispering in their ears now and promising campaign funds for the next election if they do it.
Speech: And that's a whole lot different from these fellows running up and down the halls whispering in their ears now and promising campaign funds for the next election if they do it.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: Now, I think that's going back to where we started.
Speech: Now, I think that's going back to where we started.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: That's having a government from the people.
Speech: That's having a government from the people.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: I think that's the essence of leadership, rather than cutting deals in dark rooms in Washington.
Speech: I think that's the essence of leadership, rather than cutting deals in dark rooms in Washington.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: (APPLAUSE)
Speech: (APPLAUSE)
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: CLINTON: Well, I believe in the town hall meetings; they started with my campaign in New Hampshire.
Speech: Well, I believe in the town hall meetings; they started with my campaign in New Hampshire.

Text: And I think Ross Perot has done a good job in having them.
Speech: And I think Ross Perot has done a good job in having them.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: And I, as you know, pushed for the debate to include the 209 American citizens who were part of it in Richmond a few days ago.
Speech: And I, as you know, pushed for the debate to include the 209 American citizens who were part of it in Richmond a few days ago.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I've done a lot of them, and I'll continue to do them as president.
Speech: I've done a lot of them, and I'll continue to do them as president.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: But I'd also like to point out that I haven't been part of what we're criticizing in Washington tonight.
Speech: But I'd also like to point out that I haven't been part of what we're criticizing in Washington tonight.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Of the 3 of us, I have balanced a government budget 12 times, I have offered and passed campaign finance reform, offered, pushed for and passed in public referendum lobbyist restrictions, done the kinds of things you have to do to get legislators together not only to establish consensus but to challenge them to change.
Speech: Of the 3 of us, I have balanced a government budget 12 times, I have offered and passed campaign finance reform, offered, pushed for and passed in public referendum lobbyist restrictions, done the kinds of things you have to do to get legislators together not only to establish consensus but to challenge them to change.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: And in 12 years as governor I guess I've taken on every interest group there was in my state at one time or another to fight for change.
Speech: And in 12 years as governor I guess I've taken on every interest group there was in my state at one time or another to fight for change.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: It can be done.
Speech: It can be done.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: That's why I tried to be so specific in this campaign to have a mandate, if elected, so that Congress will know what the American people have voted for.
Speech: That's why I tried to be so specific in this campaign to have a mandate, if elected, so that Congress will know what the American people have voted for.

Speech: (APPLAUSE)

Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: They want us to talk about the problems of this country.
Speech: They want us to talk about the problems of this country.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I don't think he'll be reelected because trickle down economics is a failure and he's offering more of it, and what he's saying about my program is just not true.
Speech: I don't think he'll be reelected because trickle down economics is a failure and he's offering more of it, and what he's saying about my program is just not true.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Look at the Republicans that have endorsed me.
Speech: Look at the Republicans that have endorsed me.

Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: High tech executives in Northern California.
Speech: High tech executives in Northern California.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Look at the 24 generals and admirals, retired, that have endorsed me, including the deputy commander of Desert Storm.
Speech: Look at the 24 generals and admirals, retired, that have endorsed me, including the deputy commander of Desert Storm.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Look at Sarah Brady, Jim Brady's wife, President Reagan's press secretary, who endorsed me because he knuckled under to the NRA and wouldn't fight for the Brady Bill.
Speech: Look at Sarah Brady, Jim Brady's wife, President Reagan's press secretary, who endorsed me because he knuckled under to the NRA and wouldn't fight for the Brady Bill.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: We've got a broad-based coalition that goes beyond party because I am going to change this country and make it better, with the help of the American people.

Text: CLINTON: First, I'd like to thank the commission and my opponents for participating in these debates and making them possible.
Speech: First, I'd like to thank the commission and my opponents for participating in these debates and making them possible.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I think the real winners of the debates were the American people.
Speech: I think the real winners of the debates were the American people.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I was especially moved in Richmond a few days ago when 209 of our fellow citizens got to ask us questions.
Speech: I was especially moved in Richmond a few days ago when 209 of our fellow citizens got to ask us questions.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: They went a long way toward reclaiming this election for the American people and taking their country back.
Speech: They went a long way toward reclaiming this election for the American people and taking their country back.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I want to say, since this is the last time I'll be on a platform with my opponents, that even though I disagree with Mr. Perot on how fast we can reduce the deficit and how much we can increase taxes on the middle class, I really respect what he's done in this campaign to bring the issue of deficit reduction to our attention.
Speech: I want to say, since this is the last time I'll be on a platform with my opponents, that even though I disagree with Mr. Perot on how fast we can reduce the deficit and how much we can increase taxes on the middle class, I really respect what he's done in this campaign to bring the issue of deficit reduction to our attention.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I'd like to say to Mr. Bush, even though I've got profound differences with him, I do honor his service to our country.
Speech: I'd like to say to Mr. Bush, even though I've got profound differences with him, I do honor his service to our country.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I appreciate his efforts and I wish him well.
Speech: I appreciate his efforts and I wish him well.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I just believe it's time to change.
Speech: I just believe it's time to change.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I offer a new approach.
Speech: I offer a new approach.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: It's not trickle down economics.
Speech: It's not trickle down economics.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: It's been tried for 12 years and it's failed.
Speech: It's been tried for 12 years and it's failed.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: More people are working harder for less, 100,000 people a month losing their health insurance, unemployment going up, our economy slowing down.
Speech: More people are working harder for less, 100,000 people a month losing their health insurance, unemployment going up, our economy slowing down.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: We can do better.
Speech: We can do better.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: And it's not tax and spend economics.
Speech: And it's not tax and spend economics.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: It's invest and grow, put our people first, control health care costs and provide basic health care to all Americans, have an education system 2nd to none and revitalize the private economy.
Speech: It's invest and grow, put our people first, control health care costs and provide basic health care to all Americans, have an education system 2nd to none and revitalize the private economy.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: That is my commitment to you.
Speech: That is my commitment to you.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: It is the kind of change that can open up a whole new world of opportunities to America as we enter the last decade of this century and move towards the 21st century.
Speech: It is the kind of change that can open up a whole new world of opportunities to America as we enter the last decade of this century and move towards the 21st century.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I want a country where people who work hard and play by the rules are rewarded, not punished.
Speech: I want a country where people who work hard and play by the rules are rewarded, not punished.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I want a country where people are coming together across the lines of race and region and income.
Speech: I want a country where people are coming together across the lines of race and region and income.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I know we can do better.
Speech: I know we can do better.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: It won't take miracles and it won't happen overnight, but we can do much, much better if we have the courage to change.
Speech: It won't take miracles and it won't happen overnight, but we can do much, much better if we have the courage to change.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Thank you very much.
Speech: Thank you very much.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: (APPLAUSE)
Speech: (APPLAUSE)
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: BUSH: Three weeks from now -- 2 weeks from tomorrow, America goes to the polls and you're going to have to decide who you want to lead this country to economic recovery.
Speech: Three weeks from now -- 2 weeks from tomorrow, America goes to the polls and you're going to have to decide who you want to lead this country to economic recovery.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: On jobs -- that's the number one priority, and I believe my program for stimulating investment, encouraging small business, brand-new approach to education, strengthening the American family, and, yes, creating more exports is the way to go.
Speech: On jobs -- that's the number one priority, and I believe my program for stimulating investment, encouraging small business, brand-new approach to education, strengthening the American family, and, yes, creating more exports is the way to go.

Name: George H. W. Bush

Speech: I don't believe in trickle-down government, I don't believe in larger taxes and larger government spending.

Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: On foreign affairs, some think it's irrelevant.

Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: I believe it's not.

Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: We're living in an interconnected world.

Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: The whole world is having economic difficulties.
Speech: The whole world is having economic difficulties.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: The US is doing better than a lot.
Speech: The US is doing better than a lot.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: But we've got to do even better.
Speech: But we've got to do even better.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: And if a crisis comes up, I ask who has the judgment and the experience and, yes, the character to make the right decision?
Speech: And if a crisis comes up, I ask who has the judgment and the experience and, yes, the character to make the right decision?
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: And, lastly, the other night on character Governor Clinton said it's not the character of the president but the character of the presidency.
Speech: And, lastly, the other night on character Governor Clinton said it's not the character of the president but the character of the presidency.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: I couldn't disagree more.
Speech: I couldn't disagree more.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: Horace Greeley said the only thing that endures is character.
Speech: Horace Greeley said the only thing that endures is character.
